trans-unit.source: Represents a dialog box that allows the user to choose a type.
trans-unit.target: Rappresenta una finestra di dialogo che consente all'utente di scegliere un tipo.

trans-unit.source: This class cannot be inherited.
trans-unit.target: Questa classe non può essere ereditata.

trans-unit.source: > [!NOTE] > [!INCLUDE[DeprecatedContent](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] This class prompts the user to browse a list of Windows Workflow Foundation and .NET Framework namespaces and their contained types and select a single type.
trans-unit.target: > [!NOTE] > [!INCLUDE[DeprecatedContent](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)]Questa classe richiede all'utente di sfogliare un elenco di spazi dei nomi Windows Workflow Foundation e .NET Framework e i relativi tipi contenuti e selezionare un solo tipo.

trans-unit.source: Gets the component to associate with the type browser dialog box.
trans-unit.target: Ottiene il componente da associare nella finestra di dialogo del browser di tipo.

trans-unit.source: If the property returns a valid value--anything other than a null reference (`Nothing` in Visual Basic)--the component is added to <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog>.
trans-unit.target: Se la proprietà restituisce un valore valido, ovvero qualsiasi valore diverso da un riferimento null (`Nothing` in Visual Basic), il componente viene aggiunto al <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog>.</xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog>

trans-unit.source: This property is required because <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog> implements <xref:System.ComponentModel.ISite>.
trans-unit.target: Questa proprietà è obbligatoria perché <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog>implementa <xref:System.ComponentModel.ISite>.</xref:System.ComponentModel.ISite> </xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog>

trans-unit.source: For <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog>, <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog.System.ComponentModel.ISite.Component%2A> always returns a null reference (`Nothing`).
trans-unit.target: Per <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog>, <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog.System.ComponentModel.ISite.Component%2A>restituisce sempre un riferimento null (`Nothing`).</xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog.System.ComponentModel.ISite.Component%2A> </xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog>

trans-unit.source: The <xref href="System.ComponentModel.IComponent"></xref> to bind to the <xref href="System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog"></xref>.

trans-unit.target: Ottiene il contenitore da associare alla finestra di dialogo del browser del tipo.

trans-unit.source: If <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog.System.ComponentModel.ISite.Container%2A> returns a null reference (`Nothing` in Visual Basic), <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog.System.ComponentModel.ISite.Component%2A> has not bound an <xref:System.ComponentModel.IComponent> to the <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog>.

trans-unit.source: Gets a value that indicates whether the type browser dialog is in design mode.
trans-unit.target: Ottiene un valore che indica se la finestra di dialogo di tipo browser è in modalità progettazione.

trans-unit.source: This property is required because <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog> implements <xref:System.ComponentModel.ISite>.
trans-unit.target: Questa proprietà è obbligatoria perché <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog>implementa <xref:System.ComponentModel.ISite>.</xref:System.ComponentModel.ISite> </xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog>

trans-unit.source: For <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog>, <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog.System.ComponentModel.ISite.DesignMode%2A> always returns `true`.
trans-unit.target: Per <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog>, <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog.System.ComponentModel.ISite.DesignMode%2A>restituisce sempre `true`.</xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog.System.ComponentModel.ISite.DesignMode%2A> </xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog>

trans-unit.source: Retrieves the service object for the specified type.
trans-unit.target: Recupera l'oggetto servizio per il tipo specificato.

trans-unit.source: If `serviceType` is of type <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Compiler.ITypeProvider>, <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog.System.IServiceProvider.GetService%2A> returns a service object.
trans-unit.target: Se `serviceType` è di tipo <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Compiler.ITypeProvider>, <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog.System.IServiceProvider.GetService%2A>restituisce un oggetto servizio.</xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog.System.IServiceProvider.GetService%2A> </xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Compiler.ITypeProvider>

trans-unit.source: Otherwise, <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog.System.IServiceProvider.GetService%2A> returns a null reference (`Nothing`).
trans-unit.target: In caso contrario, <xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog.System.IServiceProvider.GetService%2A>restituisce un riferimento null (`Nothing`).</xref:System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.TypeBrowserDialog.System.IServiceProvider.GetService%2A>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Type> of service object to retrieve.
trans-unit.target: Il <xref:System.Type>dell'oggetto servizio da recuperare.</xref:System.Type>

trans-unit.source: A service object of type serviceType, or a null reference ( in Visual Basic) if there is no service object of type serviceType.
trans-unit.target: Un oggetto servizio del tipo serviceType , o un riferimento null ( in Visual Basic) se non è presente alcun oggetto servizio di tipo serviceType .
